## Import Screen

Purpose:
- connect/import score sources safely

Layout:

```text
[Import Sources]
Aimlabs
- status: not connected / connected / needs sample
- action: choose folder / import file / run import

KovaaK's
- status: not connected / connected / needs sample
- action: choose folder / import file / run import

Sample Fixture
- action: import demo data

[Recent Import Batches]
Date | Source | Imported | Skipped | Review | Status

[Import Report]
Selected batch:
- imported runs
- skipped duplicates
- review items
- errors
```

Rules:
- never modify source files
- show what was imported
- show what was skipped
- show what needs review

---

## Review Queue Screen

Purpose:
- fix uncertain data

Layout:

```text
[Queue Summary]
Pending: 7
Resolved today: 3

[Review Item]
Detected scenario: "Pasu Int"
Platform: KovaaK's
Score: 850
Date: unknown

Reason:
"Scenario matched multiple possible definitions."

Suggested matches:
1. VT Pasu Intermediate
2. Pasu Reloaded
3. Create new progress-only scenario

Actions:
[Accept match] [Choose different] [Ignore run] [Save rule]
```

Rules:
- manual corrections create scenario_match_overrides
- review queue should be calm and easy
- never force fake confidence

---

## Runs Screen

Purpose:
- inspect raw performance history

Layout:

```text
Filters:
platform | benchmark | scenario | date range | matched/unmatched

Table:
Date | Platform | Scenario | Score | Match | Benchmark | Source

Side panel:
selected run raw details
source file
import batch
match confidence
```

Rules:
- table is allowed here
- not the main Home experience
- raw payload should be viewable for debugging

---

## Benchmark Sources Screen

Purpose:
- manage benchmark definitions

Layout:

```text
[Installed Definitions]
Name | Source | Version | Status | Enabled

Voltaic | Built-in | 2026.x | Valid | Enabled
Viscose | Built-in | 2026.x | Valid | Enabled
My Pack | Local CSV | 1.0 | Warning | Disabled

[Actions]
Import JSON
Import CSV
Add URL later
Validate again
View source details
Disable
Remove user-installed
```

Preview modal:

```text
Benchmark name
Source type
Scenario count
Rank count
Threshold count
Universal category coverage
Warnings
Errors
[Install] [Cancel]
```

Rules:
- built-in definitions can be disabled, not removed
- user-installed definitions can be removed
- errors block install
- warnings require confirmation

