## Settings Screen

Purpose:
- app-level settings

Sections:

```text
Data folders
Import behavior
Database backup
Appearance
Privacy
Developer/debug
```

MVP settings:
- choose app data folder only if needed
- show database location
- export diagnostics
- create backup
- reset sample data
- theme later

---

## Empty States

Every empty state should tell the user what to do.

Example Home empty state:

```text
No score data yet.
Import Aimlabs/KovaaK's data or load sample data to test Aim Brain.
[Import Data] [Load Sample Data]
```

Example Benchmark Source empty state:

```text
No benchmark definitions enabled.
Enable a built-in definition or import a benchmark source.
```

---

## Visual Direction

- dark app-like interface
- clean cards
- strong spacing
- subtle category colors
- not spreadsheet-like
- not overloaded
- coach message first, numbers second

---

## UI Anti-Patterns

Do not:
- make Home a spreadsheet
- show every metric at once
- hide import errors
- pretend unmatched data is fine
- hardcode Voltaic screens
- put analysis logic inside React components
